cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LF, cs.CL

This paper deals with logical theories and reasoning about computations, which are topics that are commonly studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of a theorem prover (Abella) for interactive reasoning, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper's focus on binding structures and their associated notions of scope, free and bound variables, and capture-avoiding substitution suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of logical frameworks (cs.LF) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
